Rate limits forced me to be intentional about how I use AI. The Pro tier offers a genuine taste of what's possible, with guardrails that force optimisation.

The optimisation rabbit hole that followed (trimming context, building tools, eyeing local LLMs) wasn't about being cheap. It was about understanding what I was actually paying for. Each constraint pushed me to think harder about what actually needed the LLM versus what could be handled locally.

Perhaps guardrails that force intentionality aren't entirely a bad thing.
